title: ASX to rebound, following Wall St, US economy expands 7.4pc
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, as investors stepped in to 'buy the dip' in New York. Big tech earnings arrive.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Dow sheds 943 points in global rout
summary: Australian shares are poised to drop 1.7pc at the open, as global equities fell hard amid a resurgent virus and widening renewed lockdowns. Oil, gold were hammered.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, global investors on edge
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower. European stocks closed lower amid virus concerns; Dow's losses accelerate, S&P 500 turns negative.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to plunge 0.9pc, Wall St plummets
summary: Australian shares are poised to fall at the open amid a fresh pandemic-paced global sell-off. The Dow fell 650 points, though it pared losses into the close. Oil drops. VIX leaps.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, earnings set to accelerate
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher as reporting season, in particular in the US, moves forward. $A edges higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge higher, Wall St rises on hopes for stimulus
summary: Australian shares are set for a modest advance as investors turn cautious amid rising global virus cases and ahead of the final US presidential debate.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall, Wall St closes down, $A surges
summary: Australian shares are poised to drop at the open with Wall Street ending lower. $A surges more than 1pc. Copper surges too.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise on renewed US stimulus hopes
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by a push by President Trump to secure more stimulus. Wall St higher. $A dips.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall, Wall St drops on stimulus, virus worries
summary: Australian shares to slide at the open as Wal St slumps, as the virus surges and stimulus talks drag on. Atlassian resets record high.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, China's GDP data in focus
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher with data on the strength of China's economy scheduled to be released on Monday.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St drifts lower
summary: Australian shares were set to open down as global equities retreated on rising COVID-19 cases. $A drops.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, US stocks fade on mixed bank earnings

author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall near 1pc at open, Wall St ends lower
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower, dragged down by global equities and rising virus cases in Europe and the US. $A slides.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, techs charge higher in New York
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher, bolstered by a strong, tech-paced rally on Wall Street. $A slips.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, S&P 500 lifts, $A leaps

title: ASX to edge up, Wall St holding modest gains
summary: Australian shares are poised - for the moment - to open slightly higher, mirroring US stocks ahead of the closing bell in New York.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Dow surges 531 points
summary: Australian shares are set to extend their post-budget gains as Wall St rebounded on hopes for an agreement on at least some fresh economic stimulus measures.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to drop after Trump abruptly ends US stimulus talks
summary: Australian shares are poised to drop, finally throwing in the towel. Wall St plunged late after the President tweeted talks with Democrats were done.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge up, Wall St lifts, oil surges
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher. Wall St rallied on hopes for more stimulus. Oil rallied as a widening strike in Norway.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, global equities on notice
summary: Australian futures are pointing to a higher open, though it remains to be seen whether sentiment will hold if US President Donald Trump's health falters.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall, techs help steady Wall St
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower. The Dow swung wildly, and managed to end in positive territory on tech buying. Oil dropped.

title: ASX to rise, Wall St pares gains into the close
summary: Australian shares are set to edge higher, though investors in the US turned cautious late as hopes for more stimulus from Washington faded. Iron ore leaps.
author: Timothy Moore
